column5: Looking for a cheap 7 day housekeeping camp with my own boat in June, Something to fill in the itch until my annual trip in july/aug. Looking around LOW or Rainy Narrows/River.Any Ideas?
Harris Hill Resort on LOW, $260 CDN for 4 nights, I'd say that's cheap
Try Stokes Bay Resort on Rainy lake

If you bring your own boat perhaps consider a motel. There's one in Sioux Narrows right by the government dock on LOTW where you could leave your boat. Restaurants, bait stores, etc close by.www.facebook.com/SiouxNarrowsMotel/ I think there are grills for cooking.Nestor Falls may have similar options.

You might want to give Miles Bay Camp a shout to see if they have a cabin open that week. They're $355 CDN per person per week. They're a boat-in and right in the heart of great walleye fishing. I can also vouch for Stokes Bay Camp on Rainy, as Camp Chef mentioned. They're a no-frills boat-in fishing camp, but I think they only have three cabins, so might be tough to get in in June.
